  56,6,becoming scattered ňĻparticles ofňļ dust
  56,7,you will ňĻallňļ be ňĻdivided intoňļ three groups
  56,8,"the people of the right, how ňĻblessedňļ will they be"
  56,9,"the people of the left, how ňĻmiserableňļ will they be"
  56,10,and the foremost ňĻin faithňļ will be the foremost ňĻin Paradiseňļ
  56,11,They are the ones nearest ňĻto Allahňļ
  56,12,in the Gardens of Bliss
  56,13,ňĻThey will beňļ a multitude from earlier generations
  56,14,and a few from later generations
  56,15,ňĻAll will beňļ on jewelled thrones
  56,16,reclining face to face
  56,17,They will be waited on by eternal youths
  56,18,"with cups, pitchers, and a drink ňĻof pure wineňļ from a flowing stream"
  56,19,that will cause them neither headache nor intoxication
  56,20,ňĻThey will also be servedňļ any fruit they choose
  56,21,and meat from any bird they desire
  56,22,And ňĻthey will haveňļ maidens with gorgeous eyes
  56,23,like pristine pearls
  56,24,ňĻallňļ as a reward for what they used to do
  56,25,There they will never hear any idle or sinful talk‚ÄĒ
  56,26,only good and virtuous speech
  56,27,And the people of the right‚ÄĒhow ňĻblessedňļ will they be
  56,28,ňĻThey will beňļ amid thornless lote trees
  56,29,clusters of bananas
  56,30,extended shade
  56,31,flowing water
  56,32,abundant fruit‚ÄĒ
  56,33,never out of season nor forbidden‚ÄĒ
  56,34,and elevated furnishings
  56,35,"Indeed, We will have perfectly created their mates"
  56,36,making them virgins
  56,37,loving and of equal age
  56,38,for the people of the right
  56,39,ňĻwho will beňļ a multitude from earlier generations
  56,40,and a multitude from later generations
  56,41,And the people of the left‚ÄĒhow ňĻmiserableňļ will they be
  56,42,ňĻThey will beňļ in scorching heat and boiling water
  56,43,in the shade of black smoke
  56,44,neither cool nor refreshing
  56,45,"Indeed, before this ňĻtormentňļ they were spoiled by luxury"
  56,46,and persisted in the worst of sin
  56,47,"They used to ask ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúWhen we are dead and reduced to dust and bones, will we really be resurrected"
  56,48,And our forefathers as well?‚ÄĚ
  56,49,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúMost certainly, earlier and later generations"
  56,50,will surely be gathered ňĻtogetherňļ for the appointed Day
  56,51,"Then you, O misguided deniers"
  56,52,will certainly eat from ňĻthe fruit ofňļ the trees of Zaqq√Ľm
  56,53,filling up ňĻyourňļ bellies with it
  56,54,Then on top of that you will drink boiling water‚ÄĒ
  56,55,and you will drink ňĻitňļ like thirsty camels do.‚ÄĚ
  56,56,This will be their accommodation on the Day of Judgment
  56,57,It is We Who created you. Will you not then believe ňĻin resurrectionňļ
  56,58,Have you considered what you ejaculate
  56,59,"Is it you who create ňĻa child out ofňļ it, or is it We Who do so"
  56,60,"We have ordained death for ňĻall ofňļ you, and We cannot be prevented"
  56,61,from transforming and recreating you in forms unknown to you
  56,62,You already know how you were first created. Will you not then be mindful
  56,63,Have you considered what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you who cause it to grow, or is it We Who do so"
  56,65,"If We willed, We could simply reduce this ňĻharvestňļ to chaff, leaving you to lament"
  56,66,‚ÄúWe have truly suffered a ňĻgreatňļ loss
  56,67,"In fact, we have been deprived ňĻof our livelihoodňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  56,68,Have you considered the water you drink
  56,69,"Is it you who bring it down from the clouds, or is it We Who do so"
  56,70,"If We willed, We could make it salty. Will you not then give thanks"
  56,71,Have you considered the fire you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who produce its trees, or is it We Who do so"
  56,73,We have made it ňĻasňļ a reminder ňĻof the Hellfireňļ and a provision for the travellers
  56,74,"So glorify the Name of your Lord, the Greatest"